First flash piece in a while, I had so much fun doing this. Over the past few months i’ve been going over this in my head a lot, and I have decided that from here on out, I will only be doing my own flash designs. These images will be set prices, and I will try my best to produce as many sheets as possible. I’m starting over and learning to do what I love again. Aside from that, I will still be doing a half-day or full day rate for any floral type sleeves. I finally have the support I need to be able to do what I enjoy, and because of this decision i will have more time to draw and produce new designs for you guys. @tommybattista @alextorresart  @jrivera_tattoos and @blackwerk_draco will be more than happy to take over anything else. Their work is 😍and they are trusted and great friends / co workers. Thank you so much to everyone who has always supported me. Tattooing is the only career I have ever been proud of. It’s the only job I have ever had where I haven’t been absolutely tortured or abused, so truly I am thankful for everyone of you. Big tattoos or small, all of you matter. For me it was either quitting tattooing or changing how I work. I’m so excited for the future. A big thank you to all the guys at the shop, but especially the best  roomate/ business partner / friend, @silverfoxtattoos_ . We have a lot of big announcements coming up, guest artists and a HUGE grand reopening of @blackoaktattoocompany and @blackoaktattoocompany I’d love to still see y’all! 💛

I’ve been on my mama / self care grind. 

Little mistakes along the way but we are human. Motherhood is so rough. 

Then Forcing yourself out of your own head. Maintaining a level of peace while suffering from serious mental health struggles every day. I am not 100% every day. I do some dumb shit sometimes acting off emotion. 

I promise you this….. Awareness, redemption and growth are powerful. 

YOOOOO Some days are easier than others. Little mamas YOU are incredibly valued. They don’t understand we are working at raising a better future. It’s not easy when you’re dealing with self hatred, feeling like you’re not doing a good job at being the only noun you have ever wanted to be. I can always be better for them. And I’ll try my best everyday. 

The amount of guilt we feel when we choose to bring life into the world, when everything is so messed up. Tear bucket is at a k2 level, and I now have a crying room, in every building I lease. it’s rough I get it. We are in this together. 🧡

This set took me so much longer than others. I started this one set when I decided to give my life to God and become completely sober. October 4. 2023. It’s been 7 months today and I finally finished the only set I have done in sobriety. It doesn’t matter if your religious, it doesn’t matter if you believe in God, or you don’t. If your follower of Jesus or not. These images are so sacred to the universe for so many reasons. I hope you enjoy them as much as I enjoyed recreating them. Now booking any of these for may-June 🧡

I’m back at work and finally booking clients again. Let’s get ittttt come see me and all my boys @allcitytattoo_ @blackoaktattoocompany @silverfoxtattoos_  @tommybattista @blackwerk_draco @alextorresart @jrivera_tattoos 🤍🤍🤍

7 months and 1 week sober today. I’ve been having such a good time that I totally forgot that seven month mark. Now making it the longest I ever made it. I have never posted photos on social media with out a filter. And while I love a good filter because let’s be honest, they make us look adorable at all times. Even when we’re not feeling the best. Or we forgot to take our meds…. 🤪. Thankfully Sobriety has given me the tools to practice self love, vulnerability, and true transparency and The best yet keeping healthy boundaries and respecting others. 😇 Trying to constantly remind myself that the true authentic Nicole, is the best version to be. God is GOOOOD. I love y’all. 🤍🌙

15 years since doing my first professional tattoo. 10 years of piercing. 🤢, 5 years a shop manager / apprentice. I built my place in tattooing. No matter what I will always own my craft. Thank you to @silverfoxtattoos_  for being a supportive business partner and helping me create a place for people to grow and do what they love. Thank you to everyone who has ever been tattooed by me / the new clients I haven’t had the pleasure of meeting yet…. And thank you to my family and friends for always supporting me and pushing me. showing me I need to stay involved in this industry. Even when,  I wanna walk away. (Like every other month) it’s hard being a business owner. Sometimes I wish I could just go in and tattoo and leave, But this is the path God chooses for me. I’m gonna continue to walk in it. I’m already excited for 2024. God, Gratitude and Growth.  And I guess tattooing BUT, #god #boundaries #mentalhealth #sobrirty and #family first. ☮️
